    "help": "Add each consent mode attribute that should be set and define the conditions for it. There can be multiple conditions for each attribute.\n\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nOnly if all defined conditions apply will the attribute be set to \"granted\". If one of the conditions is not true, the attribute is set to \"denied\".\n\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nIf a consent mode attribute is not defined here, it will not be sent unless something else is defined for it in the Consent Default Settings.\n\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nExample of \"ad_user_data\" which should be set to \"granted\" if the \"Google Ads\" service has been agreed to:\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConsent Mode Attribute: ad_user_data\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConsent Type: Service\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConsent Value: ,Google Ads,\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"
